trans-unit.source: Unit Testing in .NET Core using dotnet test
trans-unit.target: Unit Testing in .NET Core using dotnet test

trans-unit.source: This guide shows how to create an ASP.NET Core web application and the associated unit tests.
trans-unit.target: This guide shows how to create an ASP.NET Core web application and the associated unit tests.

trans-unit.source: It will start by creating a simple web service application and then add tests, and continue by creating more tests to guide implementing new features.
trans-unit.target: It will start by creating a simple web service application and then add tests, and continue by creating more tests to guide implementing new features.

trans-unit.source: The completed code is available [in the core-docs repository on GitHub](https://github.com/dotnet/core-docs/tree/master/samples/unit-testing/using-dotnet-test).
trans-unit.target: The completed code is available [in the core-docs repository on GitHub](https://github.com/dotnet/core-docs/tree/master/samples/unit-testing/using-dotnet-test).

trans-unit.source: Writing .NET Core console apps using the CLI tools: A step-by-step guide
trans-unit.target: Writing .NET Core console apps using the CLI tools: A step-by-step guide

trans-unit.source: This guide will show you how to use the .NET Core CLI tooling to build cross-platform console apps.
trans-unit.target: This guide will show you how to use the .NET Core CLI tooling to build cross-platform console apps.

trans-unit.source: It will start with the most basic console app and eventually span multiple projects, including testing.
trans-unit.target: It will start with the most basic console app and eventually span multiple projects, including testing.

trans-unit.source: You'll add these features step-by-step, building on what you've already seen and built.
trans-unit.target: You'll add these features step-by-step, building on what you've already seen and built.

trans-unit.source: A finished version of the code you'll build is located [in the core-docs repository on GitHub](https://github.com/dotnet/core-docs/tree/master/samples/core-projects/console-apps).
trans-unit.target: A finished version of the code you'll build is located [in the core-docs repository on GitHub](https://github.com/dotnet/core-docs/tree/master/samples/core-projects/console-apps).

trans-unit.source: Writing Libraries with Cross Platform Tools
trans-unit.target: Writing Libraries with Cross Platform Tools

trans-unit.source: This sample covers how you can write libraries for .NET using cross-platform CLI tools.
trans-unit.target: This sample covers how you can write libraries for .NET using cross-platform CLI tools.

trans-unit.source: They provide an efficient and low-level experience that works across any supported OS.
trans-unit.target: They provide an efficient and low-level experience that works across any supported OS.

trans-unit.source: The completed code is available [in the core-docs repository on GitHub](https://github.com/dotnet/core-docs/tree/master/samples/core-projects/libraries/frameworks-library).
trans-unit.target: The completed code is available [in the core-docs repository on GitHub](https://github.com/dotnet/core-docs/tree/master/samples/core-projects/libraries/frameworks-library).
